    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="83" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gana</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13,
                                1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge your note
                            of the 28th ultimo, submitting the suggestion of your Government that
                            the claims not decided by the American Chilean commission, which
                            recently sat at Washington, be adjusted by paying such an amount of the
                            face of such claims as the aggregate amount awarded by the commission on
                            claims which they did consider bears to the face amount of the latter
                            claims.</p>
                <pb facs="0141" n="91" xml:id="pg_91"/>
                <p>In reply I have the honor to say to your excellency that this Government
                            does not feel warranted in consenting to such an arrangement. It thinks
                            that each and every claim should be examined and settled upon its
                            merits, by an international commission.</p>
                <p>Accept, Mr. Minister, the renewed assurance of my highest
                            consideration.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
